Bug.WithStack:
Hello,
I would like to suggest an enhancement in the "source" menu itme in an editor, ie the ability to generate automatically in every subclasses of an abstract class the implementation of an abstract method.
Example :
abstract void writeOut(OutputStream out);

would generate in all subclasses something like :
abstract void writeOut(OutputStream out) {
   // TO DO...
}
would generate in all subclasses something like :
public void writeOut(OutputStream out) {
   // TO DO...
}
You can use the 'add unimplemented methods' quick fix on all subclasses.

There are currently no plans to add such a source action.
It is already what I do...but when the hierarchy of class is big (like for instance an syntatic tree), it is very painful and would be appreciated... like for instance having by default the apache common toString, hashhCode, and so on...
regards
Xavier
As of now 'LATER' and 'REMIND' resolutions are no longer supported.
Please reopen this bug if it is still valid for you.

