Bug.WithStack:
Currently the build macro resolving API knows nothing about how to handle spaces and special characters in the path build macros while resolving. As a result build macros are resolved in the buildfile with spaces and special characters intact.
We need to pass to the macro resolving API some additional argument that would tell MBS how to treat spaces and other special characters. This could be some call-back interface, e.g.
ISpecCharHandler{
String getCharValue(char ch, IBuildMacro macro)
} The spaces and special chars problem was intended to be fixed for the 3.0.2. Retargeting to the 3.0.2 Re-targetting to 3.1 Bugs still assigned to the inbox can not have the target milestone set. If someone is really going to fix this in 3.1, please assign it to yourself.

